Eni, Mediaset, Intesa Sanpaolo, UBI: Italian Equity Preview

-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 
2011-06-20T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/eni-mediaset-intesa-sanpaolo-ubi-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  rose 244.40 points, or 1.2
percent, to 20,096.84.  Eni SpA (ENI)  : Italy’s biggest oil company may sell
about 1 billion euros ($1.43 billion) in bonds to institutional
investors,  Il Sole 24 Ore  reported. In September, Eni may also
sell 2 billion euros in bonds to retail investors, the newspaper
said. Eni declined to comment, according to Il Sole. The stock
rose 1.1 percent to 15.99 euros.  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  : The company’s unit Banca
Fideuram SpA is in talks to buy Banca Network Investimenti SpA,
Il Sole 24 Ore reported. Banca Network, controlled by four
partners including Aviva Plc and Banco Popolare SC (BP IM), has
almost 500 financial promoters and about 3 billion euros under
management, Il Sole said. Intesa shares jumped 4.5 percent to
1.82 euros and shares of Banco Popolare rose 4.2 percent to 1.63
euros.  Mediaset SpA (MS)  : ITV Plc, Time Warner Inc. and News
Corp. may be interested in buying Endemol NV,  La Repubblica 
reported. Mediaset, Mediaset Espana Comunicacion SA, Cyrte Fund
II BV and Goldman Sachs Group Inc. bought Endemol in 2007.
Mediaset fell 0.2 percent to 3.39 euros.  Unione di Banche Italiane ScpA (UBI)  : The bank’s planned
capital increase will be “successful,” Corrado Faissola,
chairman of the lender’s supervisory board, told Il Sole 24 Ore.
The banks managing the share sale will guarantee its success in
spite of “the weak markets,” Faissola said in the interview.
UBI rose 0.7 percent to 3.96 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
